{"batch":"Governance & Contracts","batch_index":2,"assessments":{"package_organization":78.6},"dimension_notes":{"package_organization":{"evidence":["`holistic_context.structure.directory_profiles` reports `goseg/protocol/contracts/` has 11 files (5 production + 6 test), which crosses the '>10 files mixed concerns' threshold and is currently a flat package containing runtime contract definitions, governance metadata handling, and multiple policy/conformance tests.","`goseg/protocol/actionids/actionids.go` defines canonical namespace/action string tokens, while `goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go` rebinds those into contract-specific namespace/action types and IDs, and `goseg/protocol/conformance/fixtures_test.go` validates fixtures through `groundseg/protocol/actions` symbols, creating a split placement of closely-related protocol identity concerns.","`README.md` defines governance/quality-gate ownership at documentation level, while governance fields (`OwnerModule`, `Stability`, `SinceVersion`) are embedded in runtime catalog specs in both `goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go` and `goseg/protocol/contracts/startram_contracts.go`, so policy source-of-truth is distributed across docs and implementation packages."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","confidence":"high"}},"findings":[{"dimension":"package_organization","identifier":"protocol_identity_split_across_packages","summary":"Protocol action identity is split across multiple packages with overlapping ownership boundaries.","related_files":["goseg/protocol/actionids/actionids.go","goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go","goseg/protocol/conformance/fixtures_test.go"],"evidence":["`actionids.go` owns raw namespace/action constants (`upload`, `c2c`, `open-endpoint`, `connect`).","`protocol_contracts.go` rebuilds the same identity space as `ActionNamespace*`/`Action*` and formula-based `ContractID`s.","`fixtures_test.go` validates canonical bindings via `groundseg/protocol/actions` symbols instead of a single contract-identity source, indicating consumers depend on different identity packages."],"suggestion":"Staged reorg plan: Stage 1 create `goseg/protocol/contracts/identity/` (or `goseg/protocol/identity/`) as the sole exported owner of namespace/action/contract-id bindings and move token declarations from `actionids` plus typed bindings from `protocol_contracts.go` into it. Stage 2 keep `goseg/protocol/contracts/` focused on catalog assembly/validation and switch conformance fixtures to import the new identity package only. Stage 3 add temporary aliases in old locations (`actionids` and any `actions` bridge) marked deprecated, then remove after downstream migration. Stage 4 run import updates and validation with `go test ./protocol/contracts ./protocol/conformance ./uploadsvc/...` and then `go test ./...`.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"protocol_contract_boundary_split"},{"dimension":"package_organization","identifier":"governance_policy_scattered_between_docs_and_runtime","summary":"Governance contract policy is scattered between README policy docs and inline runtime specs.","related_files":["README.md","goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go","goseg/protocol/contracts/startram_contracts.go","goseg/protocol/contracts/family_specs_test.go"],"evidence":["`README.md` declares backend quality-gate and governance documentation ownership.","Both `protocol_contracts.go` and `startram_contracts.go` inline governance policy fields (`OwnerModule`, `Stability`, `SinceVersion`) directly in family specs.","`family_specs_test.go` constructs governance-bearing specs in tests, reinforcing that governance semantics are spread across runtime and test setup rather than a clearly isolated policy layer."],"suggestion":"Staged reorg plan: Stage 1 introduce `goseg/protocol/contracts/governance/` with a dedicated schema and per-family policy declarations (protocol/startram) as the single policy source. Stage 2 move inline governance literals from `protocol_contracts.go` and `startram_contracts.go` to that package and make catalog builders consume those declarations. Stage 3 narrow `family_specs_test.go` to validate builder behavior and add governance package tests for policy integrity/versioning rules. Stage 4 update docs links in `README.md` to the new package path and validate with `go test ./protocol/contracts ./protocol/conformance` plus `go test ./...`.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"protocol_contract_boundary_split"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["No single package is designated as canonical owner for protocol action identity plus governance metadata.","The contracts directory is operating as a flat aggregation point for runtime specs, policy semantics, and test concerns."],"likely_symptoms":["protocol_identity_split_across_packages","governance_policy_scattered_between_docs_and_runtime"],"possible_false_positives":["`avg_fan_in`/`avg_fan_out` values in `directory_profiles` are all 0.0 in this packet, so coupling-direction evidence is unavailable and was not used as a downgrade driver."]}}
